As much as I like that more Stephen King books are being made into films and some are being remade I do think trailers need to be redone.  Especially for something like this.  Instead of showing clips from the movie, just shoot a trailer as it’s own mini movie.  Here’s what could be done;

You have a shot of the pet Cemetery itself.  And the various graves.  And a voice over saying something like this; “it’s a point in our lives we all must face:  Death.  It brings such sorrow to the living.  No where moreso than when one looses someone so dear and so loved.  what if death can be cheated?  Would you dare such a risk?  Could you live with the consequences?”  
And then the shot falls upon the deadfall.  Then it cuts to black and the title comes up.
